  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The elfitor device is a small non invasive device that uses dynamic light scattering to
      measure skin bloodflow, blood velocity, coagulation and hemodynamic parameters. In this
      study, the investigators will investigate whether the elfitor device is able to detect
      changes in bloodpressure, cardiac output during general anesthesia. Furthermore, the
      investigators will investigate changes in cutanuous blood flow in different parts of the body
      during peripheral nerve or neuraxial block.Being able to monitor these entities, under- and
      overdosing of general and local anesthetics may be prevented, resulting in favorable
      hemodynamics and better intra and postoperative pain relieve.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
